content.detailedDescription: I was outside of my house with my family with a campfire and my dad was telling a story. i then heard this short and quit hum and then i looked up and i saw it. i honestly thought it was a ufo i didn't know what it was. it was in the shape of a cylinder with dome and it was moving at a steady pace. i was feeling amazed during and after it. it disappeared like it disintegrated.
content.summary: It was moving across the sky extremely quickly with a steady pace.

content.detailedDescription:
Was at home watching television when i noticed a bright light on one of my cctv cameras. i then started watching it live and also went outside to see if i could see it better. it moved from side to side, was joined by other spheres and possibly was flying at a low altitude. i noticed that some of the spheres were changing colors and shape. it appeared to be "square" but i believe the camera's relatively low resolution may have caused this. at times, they also took on a triangle shape.  

watched from several hours and then they seemed to disappear so i then went to bed at approximately 12:45am. i checked the recording that the cctv made and determined it had been there earlier than i first saw it and had reappeared during the early hours of the 8th and then disappeared. it did not return the next night.

the sighting took place on the gila river indian reservation which is just south of my location.  my house which is on the side of a hill gives me a vantage point that one would not have if on the ground.

timing on one of the files:

10:53:40 sphere is on and flashing. 
10:54:34 second sphere moves in from the west (right)
10:54:48 spheres are very bright.  second sphere is changing colors
10:54:56 second sphere disappears
10:57:23 third sphere is seen approaching from the left(east) and is   located just below the 08 on the date. it is changing colors as well.

most of the "action" takes place in the same area.  i have uploaded a picture showing the location.  it is just south of a main highway between i-10 and maricopa, az.
content.flightPath: Stationary,Hovering then path,Straight-line path,Path with directional change,Other
content.summary: Multiple spheres moving about during the night hours, joining and then separating

content.detailedDescription: I was driving toward the medical district to pick up my spouse from work.  as i approached the hospitals on st. sebastian, i saw a bright, red-orange orb hovering near the georgia regents and va hospitals.  i first thought it was a medical helicopter coming/going but realized that there were no blinking lights, just the constant red/orange, and the orb was completely still. i then checked for the antenna towers on the hospitals and saw those clearly down below the orb. as i came to the traffic light to stop, i was able to observe it another minute and then it suddenly zoomed toward the southwest.  it went so fast it was out of sight immediately; however, it left a "flame" trail as it went, similar to what you see when you quickly wave sparklers around in the air.  the flame trail dissipated a few seconds afterward.  since it wasn't a helicopter nor a plane, i thought that i must have just seen a ufo, similar to the reports of red-orange lights in the sky the local radio morning talk show had been discussing previously.
content.summary: Glowing orb hovered over medical district then zoomed away leaving fire trail

content.detailedDescription: We were sitting on the deck looking for early shooting stars.  saw 5 of those but lost interest when we started seeing these moving lights. saw and heard planes blinking, though these lights did not move when the planes were nearby. they did not track any plane. thought the first one was a satellite.  then within the next hour and 10 minutes we saw a total of 13.  most moving from south to north, a few moving from west to east. dim white star appearance.  most looked like they had smooth motion.  some looked like they wobbled and not in a smooth straight line. no sound. couldn't tell size, shape or distance. clear night. no way to confuse them with shooting stars or planes. we did not see them from horizon to horizon.  movement would just catch your eye.  we couldn't tell if they stopped and hovered, as we would lose sight of some in the milky way. i've never put in a report before.  it was a pretty weird and awesome experience i'll never forget. we lost sight of most of these in the overhead roofline and didn't have to wait very long to see another.
content.summary: At first thought was satellite- then saw 13 within 1hr10min./dim stars moving.

content.detailedDescription:
1.- i was outside our beach house rental filming an outdoor decoration that i liked for the company i work for.
2.- my daughter noticed the lights 1st and pointed them out to me.
3.- not sure until about 10 seconds later i knew they had to be ufo's
4.- there are 2 orange orbs, one to the left and one to the bottom of it but right side to the one above.  i then noticed them almost switch positions, as if they were trying to alien.  then they started separating and the bottom orb disappeared with the top one shortly after.  there were fireworks that night for the 4th of july so i knew it wasn't any firework or flare.
5.-i felt excitement, i immediately had my daughter go get my wife while i filmed the whole thing.  after was pure bliss and excitement to have seen ufo's for the 3rd time in my life.
6.- they disintegrated
content.summary: Beautiful, lights hovered but switched positions from left to right and then appart and disapeared.

content.detailedDescription: I was driving home from work on highway 169 northbound. i noticed it slowly descending in the western sky during sunset. it was falling slowly enough to catch my attention. i pulled out my phone and took a photo, then started recording. i recorded it for a little over two minutes. when i got home i showed it to my wife and she could not identify it. i posted it the next day on facebook. it attracted lots of attention. multiple people recommended i report it to this site. it may simply be a passing comet, however it's glow never dissipated and it did not give off a tail/trail behind it.
content.summary: I noticed it while driving and pulled out my phone to take a photo and film it.

content.detailedDescription:
This is not an occasional event. this is a daily ongoing problem for me.  sightings first happened approximately five to six years ago. i started seeing shadows that would change shape and size. i started noticing spots and bruising on the body. i noticed entities changing form. bruising and dark spots on my body would burn and change shape. my skin would ripple.  movement occurs under my skin. i started taking pictures, still pictures that would move. they move about in waves in lines, at the same time. lights appear on the ceiling before this happens. i found a nest of them under my bed, took a picture of it, then took it out of my home. i previously found 2 in my back yard. i stopped telling people because they began talking & looking at me like i was crazy. to this day, i am attacked 3-4 times a day. my body from head to toe is bruised and scarred, and marked with what looks like chicken pox, and they multiply daily. i cannot even show my legs because people think i have a contagious condition. i also have pictures of my body. nothing gets rid of them, but after years of trying, i have learned how to slow them down during the attack.
i look at the sky nightly and see the crafts, that most people think are stars.
content.summary: Blue and white vehicle all over bakersfield california. others seen in my home.

content.detailedDescription: Was at my uncles house in wagner, sd when my cousin and i came outside to have a smoke, soon after we came outside my cousin and myself noticed flashes of light which at first we thought were coming from the airport near by,but the object then appears in a tree about 20ft from us, flashing the entire time,it came down to our level and flashed 5 times it was a blue/white light as we watched i noticed that the flashes seem to make whatever it was look like a very small classic ufo shape(saucer), and just as it appeared it disappears..I can honestly say that it did not make me feel fear i was more amazed, my cousin and i looks at each other and we both said, "what the hell was that?" when the object wasn't emmiting light i couldn't see whatever it was evn though it was right in the driveway with street lights lighting the area.

content.detailedDescription: Was leaving house to go over to friends house.  wife left at same time in different vehicle.  right after leaving driveway, we both noticed 2 large orange objects directly above each other in the southern sky.  they were larger than any other objects out that night.  initially though it was a new radio tower, as we had never seen them before.  observed objects and discussed with wife before going about our business.  rode to my business to check the mailbox on my way out, objects were no longer in the sky. never appeared to us again, no new radio tower, and 2 close friends also observed the same described objects about 2-3 months later.

content.detailedDescription: It was may be 11 or 12 midnight i went outside from my room and  looking at  the moon and what i saw was... one object travelling really fast on the sky  and it took 90 degree right turn in such a speed and i dont know where it gone. i know that its impossible for we humans to travel in such a speed and cant take 90 degree right turn too into such an speed  in todays world.

content.detailedDescription: My house at this time had a unique stone color and shape when viewed from above in the backyard. i went outside to pick up some blowing trash . when i turned to come back inside thru the back patio i observed the object hovering stationary above my house.I went back inside to get my 10x 50 binoculars so to get a better look i had to lay flat on my back to view.I went back inside and got my cordless phone to call my brother who has a aerospace degree and works for boeing. when i returned i saw 3 jet trails one coming from the direction of luke air force base one coming from the south of me and the other from approx. the south east. when i viewed thru the binoculars i could see the one from the base was an f-16 with  missles on its wingtips . one from the south was the same . one from the southeast was a early warning jet , i could see the radar dome rotating on its  top. all 3 converged on it ascending in height ,all of a sudden all of the nine connected lights glowed along with red orange borders . it started to  ascend ,it kind of made a hissing noise. all 3 jets went up after it but the ufo went faster. all 3 jets and the ufo went beyond my view. i told my brother i could not believe what i witnessed. there was news about it briefly on the evening news station and i think they called the lights above tolleson.
content.summary: Observes 9 glowing white lights orange glow around white all together directly above my house

content.detailedDescription: My wife and i were sitting on our back porch at approximately 10 pm on 08/09/15. we generally sit on the porch early morning and each evening for about an hour, just relaxing and talking. about 10:20 pm we both noticed a pulsating light about 40 deg. above the horizon to the s-sw. the light was pulsating on about a 2 second interval from bright to dim to bright again. we keep a small pair of binoculars on the porch to watch birds, squirrel, deer, etc. looking through these, we could see that this light was actually 2 lights side by side. i got a stronger pair of binoculars from the house and was able to clearly see that these were indeed two lights on what appeared to be an oval object of dark gray. while we were watching this object, a single smaller bright light approached it from the south, at t a fairly slow speed. this second object did not pulsate, remaining constant. as it approached the pulsating object, it slowed even more until it merged with it. after approximately 30 more seconds, the pulsating light object blinked out and was seen no more.
content.summary: Observed ufo, pulsating light

content.detailedDescription:
Sunday august 9th 2015, toronto trinity bellwood park, public drum circle:

at around 2 or 3 or so many people all observed a stationary bright star in the blue sky above the drum circle.  theories were many, but the only ones that made sense were weather balloons, stationary satellite reflection, or super-nova.  we could rule out planets, all the bright planets are in leo with the sun and this was well over 90 degrees away from the sun in the middle of blue sky.

it disappeared and i was excited to maybe here about a supernova in the news.

drum circle ended at 6 then there was a yoga and sound therapy class that evolved out of the circle.  while laying in the grass after one of the exercises (6:45-ish) i noted/ blurted out "hey there is that star again!"

a few people took notice with me and i would have just let it go myself, until two other identical looking stars moved from left(east) to right(west) at slightly different speeds then each other passing by the central un-moving "star".

naturally i got up and left the yoga area and excitedly got the attention of other drum circle people who were relaxing and socializing on the lawn.  i showed them the moving two stars flying in slightly undulating yet mostly straight paths in the blue sky,  a small crowd of maybe 8 people gathered and we discussed;  then to our excitement two more "stars" following the same flight path appeared in the west headed east and got very close together like the previous two had and slowly disappared, then two more came except these last two (last of three pairs that we observed moving) got close to the stationary star and then slowed there movements substancially and headed north and south slowly out from the one stationary star.

these two slowly disappeared over the course of 30 minutes.  clouds would come and go blotching out the one stationary star that remained through-out the observation of the other 6 moving objects.  then we noticed that the stationary star had moved higher during one of it's 'blotchings out'  then with maybe 15 people watching the one star that had not moved slowly ascended higher and higher above us to the point where you had to look straight up (uncomfortable for the neck) to see it.  

we all said our prayers for it to come visit us and such.  then me and my friend went to go get some food as dusk began.  probably should have sat and observed it for dusk to see if it emmited it's own light after sundown but we didn't think of it at the time. it was probably around 8 when we left the park, during the long walk we would turn around and still see it high high in the sky.

the two obvious interpretations i have are:

1) weather balloons; maybe with different chemicals lifting them, different weight loads, different propulsion systems???  though the major problem with this is why would the 6 'initially moving' ones all start and follow the same path and then the last two have very different outcomes, why were they able to pass the one stationary one, would the stationary one not have been in the same currents??

2) e.T.Craft:  alot of the earth is pretty boring and we were having alot of fun, so yeah, makes sense they'd want to stop by and observe us -- hahaha.
content.flightPath: Stationary,Hovering then path,Straight-line path,Path with directional change,Path then hovering
content.summary: Bright "stars" that moved during daylight, over drum circle.

content.detailedDescription:
My wife and i were in our back yard, looking for shooting stars, during the perseid meteor shower. we had seen quite a few on august 8th and 9th. we had also seen various other (slow) moving lights, moving in various directions, which we have always called "satellites".

when the triangle formation first came into view, i pointed to it, and thought that it was a shooting star. while following it, by pointing it out to my wife, i realized the there were three lights (not a shooting star).

the "object" started in the northern sky, slightly west of being directly overhead. it was moving pretty quickly, but not as fast as some of the shooting stars i've seen. it moved directly toward the south, and i lost sight of it, as it became "washed out" in the lights of the city. the total sighting lasted about 8 or 9 seconds (roughly).

one of the lights was at the "front", and the other two were at the "back". there was no flashing of any kind, and the white lights appeared to be all of the same brightness, and did not fluctuate.

even though i was pointing at it, and following it with my finger, my wife was not able to see it. afterward, i just could not believe what i saw, trying to think of any explanations that i could. i couldn't, so i'm submitting this.
content.summary: White lights in triangle formation, quickly moved from north to south in straight line. no noise.

content.detailedDescription: I was taking some tree photo's when i looked up, i seen a "black hole" forming in a clear blue sky, this is not the first. 5 craft's came out of it, not the same shape. then it "closed". later another "black hole" came out and a cluster of cigar shaped craft's came out. then after about 5 minutes they re entered the "black hole" and it just closed up and was gone. these are just a very few of the photo's i done that day... much, much more to all of this. i am a former osi officer in the usaf, a well respected businessman in our area, i don't waste my time with hoax crap. many of my friends who are still with the government said the one like the kecksburg crash is very strange!
content.summary: 5 craft's, not all the same shape came out of what you could call a "black hole", much more to this!

content.detailedDescription:
I was sat in my garden relaxing and drinking a weak mix of pimms and lemonade, my second or third glass, i had already eaten and was not intoxicated.

it was 10:15pm (+/- 5 minutes) and the sun was well set, a clear night i was enjoying the starry view and waiting for a pass of the iss. i am not totally inexperienced at skywatching and can usually tell a plane or balloon quite easily.

the triangle object(s) appeared over rooftop to my south-west on an apparent northerly heading. after around 3-4 seconds on that heading it seemed to curve to turn to a north-west direction and after a further 3-4 seconds was gone over trees. the three orange lights were not very bright and seemed to fade a little more as the object moved away. i could not see if the space between the orange corner lights was filled by some rigid body, i do not recall seeing the stars being masked by it but can not say for sure either way as the orange lights were really the focus of my eyes. my initial feeling was that the object was perhaps 15-20m above ground (approx twice the house height) and moving at somewhere around 20-30 kph. i at first thought the size were in the range of 2m to 4m, along each edge. but after further consideration there was nothing to truly indicate the distance, so no way of telling the size or speed. during the apparent turn the triangle shape seemed to alter slightly this gave the impression of a gentle change in orientation, i can't say for sure if the triangle was true equilateral. 

the object were totally silent, during the event my mind raced and i quickly wondered if i were watching a kite or drone, but there was no noise or breeze at all. the object passed over multiple properties and fenced boundaries and beyond some trees, a terrible place to try and fly a drone or kite anyway.

i have also considered birds, in fact it is the only explanation i could consider at this time, but they were three very large and silent birds with highly reflective bellies and invisible wings, and able to fly in a excellent triangle formation. i have since watched for bird formations on the subsequent evenings and seen nothing of the sort.
content.summary: Triangle shape, visually similar to famous belgian ufo image but with no central light, just three yellow-orange corners.

sent from my iphone

content.detailedDescription: May 10th, around 310 pm. time may be hour off. my digital camera may be set incorrectly. if important contact me i will check. standing outside century 21 w/nikon d7000-18-200mm lens doing architectural shots. took several pointing toward buildings, west. did not see object. photo taken 250th of second so this makes sense. on the subway home reviewing shots, even tho i need reading glasses which i did not have on i noticed something in sky and put glasses on and was amazed to see a white  cylindrical shaped object cloud color w/linear line going across the bottom of object. tho it is obvious is not a lenticular cloud. object in west sky pointing down/northward at a 300 degree angle. arriving home uploaded to nikon view/transfer/put thru nikon capture program to change raw/nef file to tiff, then to photoshop to make it a jpg. as seen in photo. this is the first time i have photographed ufo. tho once not certain of date, around 1969 night was in neighborhood park bailey ave park, bronx ny, 233rd st. believe i was looking eastward. saw object looked like full moon. could not have been moon because there appeared what looked to be craft, 2? i think, at the time i thought they were air force fighter jets. frozen just aside the object and they would have had to be hundreds of miles across if this were the moon so it must have been a smaller object. and there was a green mist surrounding object. i recall hearing on the news not to worry that there was an airforce test in ny. i cannot attest however that this was the same event. but the event i do absolutely recall. tho i cannot recall the exact year, or whom i was with. i was with one or 2 childhood friends. i was approx 12-14 at the time. file size provided. if absolutely necessary i can provide larger; nef, tiff, jpg, & or i can send the memory card, but only if you feel this is an interesting shot and would be worthy. i have 2 cards. one is hidden elsewhere,not in my home. i did this in case i needed to prove the event. honestly this object appears to be a real solid object. i have been shooting pictures since 1970. began developing my own film in 71 have had various cameras probably 25 in all. i still shoot film, more than several lenses. have experienced all kinds of abberations and lens flare, in this image you can see some lens flare. i believe. the typical type but this does not to me appear to be that. and i know of no type of artifacting typical of digital either. i have images with getty, not many and am familiar with overprocessing and it's effects.  this image was sharpened slightly, and contrast enhanced slightly. i may have increased color a bit but that is all. please contact me and let me know your thoughts on this object.
content.summary: Taking architecture photo 250th of a second, noticed later that there was object,  cylindrical in sky. white, some linear pattern at bottom covering diameter of object. object at angle pointing downward. 330 degrees toward right, or north.

content.detailedDescription: My friend and myself were on holiday in hay on wye nor wales. we stood outside to have a smoke and looked up to the sky because it was so clear and lots of stars. we saw a plane go by quite high up then we noticed a light moving from our right. it was dim and we had to really look hard to follow it.....Then my friend said " look it's just stopped" i said "no it hasn't look it's over to the left" it was then we realised ther was two of them....The one furthest left then also stopped. the one on the left adjusted its path lower to be on line with the first one and they both just stopped there for a few minutes and i am certain beams were coming out of them both towards the other but no explosion or anything it was as if they were communicating with each other we watched them for about 4 more minutes and then both lights just shot off upwards at extreme speed and we couldn't see them anymore. we were convince these were not planes or shooting stars because they manoeuvred in a way stars don't and were so high , too high to be planes....We are convinced that these were some sort of ufos. we were excited and happy. i am 60 years old and have had an interest in the subject since my teens but this is the first time i've seen anything like this....
content.summary: Two lights going to our left one in front then both stopped and adjusted to be in line with each other

content.detailedDescription:
i couldn't sleep, so i went out to the patio of my apartment to have a smoke around 3:00 a.M.  i looked up at the sky as i always do, and noticed what i thought was a star that was bigger and brighter than the others, just above the tree across the parking lot.  it was far away, but visible just above the treeline.

as i looked at it i saw it moving just a bit, and this really got my attention.  it lowered to just below the top of the tree and i could still see it through the leaves. it didn't move fast, it just eased down, but there was no doubt it was being propelled. it also appeared to be flickering, and there seemed to be different colors flickering in at times.  i was excited and a little scared.

it basically hovered there for a while, moving just a bit from time to time.  i got spooked and went back in.  my curiosity won after just a few minutes and i went back out. now it was a quite a ways above the tree and just hanging there.  i watched it for a very long time, and occasionally it would move to the side and up a bit - maybe just a few hundred feet at a time - hard to really say how far it actually moved.  again it wasn't a super-fast move, but definitely propelled. now that it was a little farther away, i felt safer (silly i know), and was just fascinated.

after a while, it's way up in the sky and just hanging there. all of the sudden it starts moving a little faster, but in small spurts, like it really might be about to go somewhere.  well, about that time.Out of the corner of my eye, i see a red, teardrop shaped craft cruising across the sky just above the treeline to my right - again, it was far away, but much closer than the one i had been watching, and very easy to see. i immediately shifted my attention to it.

all i could tell was that it appeared dark in the center, but definitely had a translucent red border (like an aura maybe) around the entire perimeter.  it was moving at a pretty good clip - i'd say it was in my sight for my 5 seconds.  quiet as a mouse - it didn't make a sound. (jaw dropped) i'm not sure why this didn't really scare me - i was just in awe.

then, about 5 minutes later, there was a flash in the sky in the general area the craft had passed through.  it wasn't huge, but i would say it was fairly big, and the best way i know to describe it was like a flash on a camera, but it had a star shape to it.  again - not a sound.

my neighbor two doors down, has 4 large grow-lights on his patio that he keeps on all night for his garden.  well i'd say about another five minutes after the flash in the sky, his grow-lights flicked off and on 4-5 times.  this is when i got really spooked and quickly went in the house. then i got to thinking it was close to daylight, so maybe his lights were on a timer, and they were just shutting down.

i waited about 10 minutes and stuck my head out, and his lights were burning bright, with no flickering.

i only stuck my head out a couple of times after that, and the craft way up in the sky was still there.  i just went out for the last time about 5:45 a.M. central time - daylight is just beginning to break, and the craft is gone.

i've always wanted to see a ufo - looks like i got my wish! wow!
content.summary: Bright flickering, moving star-like object.

content.detailedDescription: It was back in late 1980s , very cloudy an dark ,around 5am.There were no other stars out , i was fueling up my truck and while looking up in the sky i noticed a light , strange because there were no stars out at all ,i finished fueling and watched the light .It went out then came back on.The light showed up in various spots in the cloudy sky,then it moved into another location, i ran in an got my boss ,i pointed it out but he went back inside.I continued watching, the light moved over in a area of a wooded field, witch are houses now, but i watched this light and it all of sudden started to releasing a lighted glitter type substance that came out of it ,it just stayed in the same spot for a while ,then sim to go higher into the night sky ,and then just like that it was gone ! i got cold chilled i've seen strong things in the sky.But this was the most strangest, i believe the is life on other planets,and i believe there watching us ,just like we are watching them.I believe i saw a ufo that night , still to this day i've never saw anything like that , meet as hell ,i believe.
content.summary: Light in sky ,watched it
